## ðŸ“‹ What You're Uploading

This is what the Firebase CLI command sends:

```json
{
  "appName": "AccreditEx",
  "primaryColor": "#4f46e5",
  "defaultLanguage": "en",
  "defaultUserRole": "TeamMember",
  "passwordPolicy": {
    "minLength": 8,
    "requireUppercase": false,
    "requireNumber": false,
    "requireSymbol": false
  },
  "globeSettings": {
    "baseColor": "#1e293b",
    "markerColor": "#818cf8",
    ...
  },
  "appearance": {...},
  "notifications": {...},
  "accessibility": {...}
}
```

This file is: `appSettings.json` (already in your project!)

---

## âœ… Verification Checklist

After uploading, check:

- [ ] Command executed without errors
- [ ] Firebase CLI returned success message
- [ ] `firebase firestore:get` shows your data
- [ ] Browser DevTools (F12) shows no errors
- [ ] App loads within 30 seconds
- [ ] No "LoadingScreen" stuck

